The intersection of two sets is the set of elements that are common to both sets. In this case, the intersection of set A and set B is:

A ∩ B = {2, 4}

The union of two sets is the set of all elements that are in either set. In this case, the union of set A and set B is:

A ∪ B = {1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 8}
